===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かえで|alt=槭,槭樹}}
{{swp|ja:カエデ}}
{{swp|Maple}}
[[File:Acer_palmatum_002.JPG|thumb|250px|{{lang|ja|楓}} (''kaede''): '''[[maple]]''' leaves and seeds.]]

{{IPAchar|/kaperu te/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaperude/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaferude/}} → {{IPAchar|/kafede/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaede/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=かえで|かへるて}}, as this word first appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' of 759 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref><ref>{{RQ:Man'yōshū|8|1623}}, text online [https://web.archive.org/web/20201123194606/http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man8Yos.html#1623 here]</ref>

Originally a compound of {{ja-com|sort=かえで|蛙|かえる|t1=[[frog]]|手|て|t2=[[hand]]}}, from the way the [[palmate]] leaves resemble a frog's foot, with the ''te'' changing to ''de'' due to {{rendaku|かえで}}, and the ''ru'' dropping out over time.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|かえで|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}

