{{U:ja:biology|カツラ}}

The ''katsura'' reading is rare for this kanji. When referring to the ''katsura'' tree, the {{ja-l|桂}} spelling is used more often to avoid confusion.

===Etymology 4===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|おかつら|alt=男桂:archaic}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=おかつら}}. Alternative spelling for {{ja-r|男%桂|お%かつら|[[male]] [[katsura]]}}, an archaic name for the katsura tree.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> Appears with this reading in the {{m|ja|和名類聚抄|tr={{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}}}, a Japanese dictionary of Chinese characters completed in 938.
